<HL>
   Who's News:
   Coca-Cola Appoints
   Senior Vice President
   For U.S. Marketing
</HL>
<DATE>
04/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS KO
</CO>
<LP>
   ATLANTA -- Coca-Cola Co., as expected, named Theodore J.
Host, president of Boyle-Midway Household Products Inc., as
senior vice president, marketing, for Coke's domestic
division.
   The appointment of the 44-year-old Mr. Host fills a
two-year vacancy in the job. Mr. Host, who joins Coke May 1,
will report to Ira C. Herbert, president of CocaCola USA, the
soft-drink company's domestic marketing arm.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   At Boyle-Midway, Mr. Host oversaw products including
Woolite, Black Flag and Easy Off. Last month, American Home
Products Corp. agreed to sell its BoyleMidway division for
$1.25 billion to Reckitt &amp; Colman PLC, a London-based
consumer products maker. Mr. Host was also an executive with
American Home's food division, whose products include Chef
Boyardee.
   Mr. Host declined to comment.
</TEXT>
